<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Congruence_classes">Congrue=
nce classes <span class=3D"anchor" id=3D"Residue"></span><span class=3D"anc=
hor" id=3D"Residue_class"></span><span class=3D"anchor" id=3D"Congruence_cl=
ass"></span></h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsecti=
on-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=
=3DModular_arithmetic&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit sect=
ion: Congruence classes"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection=
-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The congruence relation is an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E=
quivalence_relation" title=3D"Equivalence relation">equivalence relation</a=
>. The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Equivalence_class" title=3D=
"Equivalence class">equivalence class</a> modulo <span class=3D"texhtml mva=
r" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span> of an integer <span class=3D"texht=
ml"><i>a</i></span> is the set of all integers of the form <span class=3D"t=
exhtml"><i>a</i> + <i>k m</i></span>, where <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" st=
yle=3D"font-style:italic;">k</span> is any integer. It is called the <b>con=
gruence class</b> or <b>residue class</b> of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a</=
i></span> modulo&nbsp;<span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m</i></span>, and may be d=
enoted <span class=3D"texhtml">(<i>a</i> mod <i>m</i>)</span>, or as <span =
class=3D"texhtml"><span style=3D"text-decoration:overline;"><i>a</i></span>=
</span> or <span class=3D"texhtml">[<i>a</i>]</span> when the modulus <span=
 class=3D"texhtml"><i>m</i></span> is known from the context.
</p><p>Each residue class modulo&nbsp;<span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m</i></spa=
n> contains exactly one integer in the range <span class=3D"mwe-math-elemen=
t mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-m=
athml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/=
Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle 0,...,|m|-1}">
  <semantics>
